Superstar DJ and house music producer, Black Coffee’s reign just won’t let up. In addition to working on his much-anticipated 6th studio album while touring and performing around the world, the 42-year-old is now becoming a household name on an international scale. The DJ, real name Nkosinathi Maphumulo, has been revealed as the August cover star of UK-based magazine, DJ Mag. DJ Mag is a British monthly magazine dedicated to electronic dance music and the DJs who bring the hits to dancefloors all over the world. The magazine calls Black Coffee “The South African superstar who keeps giving back”. Check out the cover ???????????? @djmagofficial A post shared by  Black Coffee (@realblackcoffee) on Jul 27, 2018 at 5:49am PDT  